Database Diagrams
...

// Use DBML to define your database structure

// Docs: https://dbml.dbdiagram.io/docs

  

Table user {
  username text [primary key]
  email text
  password text
  friends array[text]
}

  

Table deck {
  id text [primary key]
  name text
  cards array[card]
  share_link text
  read_access array[text]
  write_access array[text]
}

  

Table review {
  id text [primary key]
  date timestamp
}

  

Table card {
  id text [primary key]
  deck_id text
  latest_review text
  creator text
  name text
  front text
  back text
  read_access array[text]
  write_access array[text]
}

  

Ref: card.id < deck.cards
Ref: card.latest_review - review.id
Ref: card.creator > user.username
Ref: card.read_access > user.username
Ref: card.write_access > user.username

Ref: deck.id > card.id
Ref: deck.read_access > user.username
Ref: deck.write_access > user.username

Ref: user.friends > user.username
